    narr:generatedFrom "d1b09a828565de86" ;
    narr:narration """This hub gathers Scarlet's pervasive **rule-of-three / tricolon** as a style primitive operating at several scales. At the phrase scale, triads recur as memorable scaffolding: [life/health/identity](narr:StyleObs_RuleOfThree), [what-you-know / how-it's-changed / IP-as-code](narr:StyleObs_RuleOfThree_1), [the direction differentiator](narr:StyleObs_RuleOfThree_Direction), and [propagation across roles/tools/contexts](narr:StyleObs_RuleOfThree_Propagation). At the taxonomy scale it structures content models — [Information/Perspective/Wisdom](narr:StyleObs_RuleOfThreeTaxonomy), the [three interview outputs](narr:StyleObs_RuleOfThreeOutputs), and [Creation/Architecture/Infrastructure layers](narr:StyleObs_RuleOfThree_Layers). At the sentence/section scale it appears as [three-sentence summaries](narr:StyleObs_ThreeLineSummary) and a [staccato tricolon](narr:StyleObs_ShortPunchyTricolon). The pattern is named meta-explicitly — [\"three altitudes of the same primitive\"](narr:StyleObs_AltitudeTaxonomy) and an [author-enforced three-sentence rule](narr:StyleObs_ThreeSentenceRule). Adjacent forms sit alongside: a [negative anaphoric triad](narr:StyleObs_NegativeParallelism) and a [numbered convergence-of-three](narr:StyleObs_NumberedConvergence) (both `related`, not `broader`). Recurrent idiolect markers — Rumsfeld framework, OS-bootloading metaphors — appear in the conviction and memory observations.""" ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleObs_11> ;
